{
  "texts": [
    "For this task, the ShapeNet dataset is used, along with the Chamfer Distance (CD) (14) as the loss function.",
    "The combination of these two tasks is used for unsupervised learning applications.",
    "By Han et al. (2019) PC-VAE was proposed, which trains its VAE architecture by creating multiple viewpoints for each 3D object, then the method divides them into a front half and a back half, based on the geodesic distance.",
    "The Euclidean distance is ignored because it causes non-semantic splitting, as suggested by Crane et al. (2017).",
    "By learning to reconstruct parts of the objects from different angles, this method simultaneously learns global and local features, along with the relationship between them, like geometric and structural information, resulting in unsupervised training, which makes the model capable of generating new objects as well."
  ]
}